[i|## title: Esoteric programming languages|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|## date: "2026-04-28"|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|## Introduction|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|A while back, I became interested in esoteric programming|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|languages. More specifically, I became interested in the|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|mechanisms involved in interpreting and compiling their|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|code. It’s a little-known field in the world of computer|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|science, yet I find this culture to be very rich and|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|challenging. That’s why I wanted to talk about it here, in|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|the form of a blog post. This is mainly my personal|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|perspective and feedback; the views expressed are my own.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|## Definition|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|An esoteric programming language is a programming language|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|designed around one or more strange or unusual ideas.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|Generally, these languages are created as a joke or to meet|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|a challenge, and are not intended to solve any specific|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|problem.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
