[i|## Culture and Community|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|There are a vast number of esoteric programming languages,|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|and new ones are created every day, often accompanied by an|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|interpreter written by the language’s creator.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|### Esolang|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|We are fortunate to have the Esolang website. It is a wiki|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|dedicated to esoteric programming languages, an excellent|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|resource for their documentation, and one of the main hubs|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|of this active community. The website allows authors to add|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|wiki pages to document their languages. These pages are then|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|indexed on other pages dedicated to listing languages by|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|category, paradigm, year, etc.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[h|Esolang|URL:https://esolangs.org/|esolangs.org|443]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|I have used this website extensively as my primary reference|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|for esoteric language specifications. The website is|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|comprehensive and updated daily.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|### Challenge|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|Since most of these languages started out as jokes, they are|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|actually used to create more unusual challenges. As shown in|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|this code golf where you have to create a Brainfuck|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|interpreter, this YouTube video, or the game Brainfuck|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|Challenge. This inspired me to create this project, which|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|brings together my implementations of interpreters and|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|compilers for esoteric programming languages.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[h|code golf|URL:https://codegolf.stackexchange.com/questions/84/interpret-brainfuck|codegolf.stackexchange.com|443]
[h|YouTube video|URL:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NFsu2E-45e0|www.youtube.com|443]
[h|Brainfuck Challenge|URL:https://store.steampowered.com/app/3708560/Brainfuck_Challenge|store.steampowered.com|443]
[h|this project|URL:https://github.com/theobori/eso|github.com|443]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|### Passion and Curiosity|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|One might wonder why people continue to invent new esoteric|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|languages, since there is no financial gain to be had. I|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|think the main reasons are passion and curiosity. A passion|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|for computer science and programming, and the curiosity to|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|seek out alternative things on the Internet.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|## Humans Only|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|Despite all the hype surrounding generative AI, I get the|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|impression that esoteric languages remain a field studied|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|largely by human minds alone. This can be explained by the|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|lack of commercial objectives; after all, the authors and|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|developers of these languages aren’t getting paid.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|Furthermore, it’s a subject that doesn’t interest companies|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|because they can’t make a profit from it, and it’s not a|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|topic that comes up in business settings either. It’s not a|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|mainstream computer science subject, and demand is very low.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|In the end, only enthusiasts and the curious remain—those|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|who simply want to have fun.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|An esoteric programming language that isn’t a product of the|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|human mind loses all its charm and appeal. These languages|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|are complex for the human brain, but much less so for an|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|artificial brain, such as an LLM.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|## Conclusion|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|It was an interesting experience to explore the world of|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|esoteric programming languages. I realized there is an|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|active community and a large number of software projects. I|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|didn’t delve any deeper—some languages are very complex—but|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|if you’re curious, I invite you to check out the Esolang|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|wiki.|/|tilde.pink|70]
[h|Esolang|URL:https://esolangs.org/|esolangs.org|443]
[i||/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|I plan to continue implementing interpreters and compilers|/|tilde.pink|70]
[i|for esoteric languages in the future!|/|tilde.pink|70]

